00:22:38.300 --> 00:22:41.610
that we could get access to.

00:22:41.610 --> 00:22:43.920
One of the downsides of
satellite data, of course,

00:22:43.920 --> 00:22:45.830
is that it's only
part of the picture.

00:22:45.830 --> 00:22:47.497
It's only environmental data.

00:22:47.497 --> 00:22:49.080
I suspect that some
of the things that

00:22:49.080 --> 00:22:52.890
are driving these patterns are
actually species interactions,

00:22:52.890 --> 00:22:55.860
changes in the amount
of insect damage

00:22:55.860 --> 00:22:57.510
as you move from
outside to inside

00:22:57.510 --> 00:23:00.540
the city, which we know is
more important at southern

00:23:00.540 --> 00:23:03.630
latitudes, and could explain
some of these stronger clines.

00:23:03.630 --> 00:23:06.360
But of course, you can't get
insect-plant interactions

